    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-08-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-08-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="1672"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1672">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 419.11 D 29/14a.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-08-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 22, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Relative to the affair at Cocoa Grove on July 4; to the killing of Pelote and
                    arresting of certain persons on the Canal Zone by Panaman police; to the War
                    Department’s request and your recommendation that demand be made for dismissal
                    of Quijano, and to your recommendation as to de la Ossa—you will immediately
                    repeat the demand for the removal of Quijano if he has not already been removed,
                    and will demand removal of de la Ossa; you will at the same time say that it is
                    expected that these officers will not be reinstated. Use all proper means to
                    cause their removal by the present administration.</p>
                <p>In regard to Ralph W. Davis, say that it is obvious that this Government expects
                    every proper effort to be made to identify the murderers of Davis, and to
                    adequately punish not only them, but all other guilty officers.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Adee.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
